description: For sale: $283,900. You must see this beautiful north woods themed cabin! Easy maintenance with custom wood furniture included. Right on the edge of the Boundary Waters and MOVE IN READY! Check out the 2 large 2nd floor bedrooms (each with a sitting area). Notice the partially completed bunkhouse for guests above the garage. With well placed windows, wood accents and tasteful decor, this cabin exudes brightness and peace. Iron Lake has walleye, Northerns and some large Bluegills AND is close to a well known Splake lake.  While this house is currently used seasonally, it is well insulated for winter use (6 inch walls).  YES! The county maintains and plows the road to Iron Lake! High speed internet is ready to be connected for those who want to work remotely. Only 37 miles from Grand Marais. This is 1 of 8 private homes on Iron Lake. Jump into your BWCA adventures.

Brand new septic system and a large detached 3 car garage.

description: For sale: $425,000. Devil Track Lake Home - ready to enjoy.  Fully furnished and all you need is the key......literally.  Devil Track Lake Home 215 is an updated 2-story home located along the shores of Devil Track Lake just 8 miles up the scenic Gunflint Trail from Grand Marais. Inside you'll find modern decor with a flare of up north touches.  Enjoy the lake-facing deck or step out of the lower-level patio doors and enjoy the spacious backyard that leads up to the lake's edge.    The home has 3 bedrooms and 2.5 bathrooms, including a spacious master suite on the main level.  In addition to the two living areas, there's a full sized kitchen and a dining room area, a perfect gathering place for the entire family.  Unique artwork and carefully selected furnishings make this home warm and welcoming.  The beautiful wall to wall windows allow you to take full advantage of the Devil Track Lake views year round.  New roof, stain, decking, flooring, newer appliances and more.  No work required on your part.      Walk down to the beach with a fishing rod, or dip your feet into the water - it does get warm in the summer!  In the winter it can be hard to tell where the land ends and the lake begins as you enjoy the expansive views of crystal white snow.  Enjoy swimming, fishing, boating, water in the warm months.  Then come back in the winter to enjoy snowmobiling, ice fishing and more with  easy access to snowmobile trails and other area lakes.   This home is the ideal place to set up your year-round base for  adventure while being just minutes away from beautiful downtown Grand Marais.  The property is part of the Landing at Devil Track Homeowner's Association  providing year round access, snow removal, maintained road and driveway, lawn care and covenants designed to protect your investment.    This home is currently part of the Cascade Vacation Rental program.  New owner's can elect multiple options how best to use and enjoy their new vacation property.

description:
For sale: $1,995,000. Greenwood Lodge - This unique property offers the ultimate private family compound or corporate retreat.
This lodge was built in 1936 by the owner of the Boston Red Sox from pines on the shores of 2,043 acre
Greenwood Lake. Then owned by the founding owner of the MN Vikings. Buildings can sleep 24 in beds. 156
acres with over 1 mile of shoreline. Be self sufficient off grid with 2 large diesel generators for
months of power. Satellite internet/TV installed. Miles of hiking and ATV trails. Hike to your own
massive granite ridge towering over the lake. Fully furnished in classic Minnesota Lodge Style. 30 min
drive to Grand Marais MN, a harbor town on Lake Superior. Development potential. Off location caretaker
wishes to stay on.

description: For sale: $359,000. All this just a 10 minute drive away from downtown Grand Marais. A beautiful home in Beautiful Cook County.

description: For sale: $395,000. Truly exceptional Grand Marais home. Located on a corner lot right in the heart of Grand Marais. Beautiful gardens, fruit trees, flowers - all professionally landscaped. Wrap around decks (682' sq.feet) Seasonal lake view. Loads of living space, 4 Bedrooms and 3 baths, 3 fireplaces - 2 gas and one wood burning.  The kitchen is wonderful! Very large with large windows and patio door to the deck, gourmet style, lots of cabinets and even a gas fireplace. Living/great room with open stair to the maser suite upstairs. This custom addition was designed and built by a local builder in 2008. The cozy room is flooded with light, has a wood fireplace and patio door to the deck. All the windows are Anderson "Eagles" for comfort all seasons. This home has endless possibilities. The office/den could be the 5th bedroom. The garage is 2 car but half used by the seller as a heated shop. Easily converted back.

description: For sale: $173,000. Brand new 3 bedroom, 1 bath home in a quiet neighborhood of Grand Marais.  Designed to be energy efficient and low maintenance in every respect, just to increase the affordability. The beautiful oak kitchen cabinets are complimented by stainless steel appliances including dishwasher and microwave vented hood and there is an island, which provides work space and extra seating.  The dining area is flanked by sliding doors to a future deck/patio. Generous windows brighten the entire living area. There is a laundry closet complete with washer and dryer hook-ups. Add the 2 stall garage for a complete package.  This home is part of a single family home development, that are all being sold through the Community Land Trust program, in which households purchase the house and lease the land. There are some fantastic loan programs that have been put together with a variety of different Housing Programs all focused on getting QUALIFIED buyers into homes with as low as $1000 down, which is less than getting into a rental.  The cost of monthly payments for purchasing this home is very competitive and even in some cases, less than rental payments.

For sale: $310,000. 1910 modern art deco home covered in cedar and slate. Landscaped in designer block and gardens. The double door entry hosts a spacious 1/2 bath and walk-in closet. Vinyl floors. The entry leads into a 20x20 family/dining room with fireplace and oak hardwood floor. Opening into the12x12 hickory and granite kitchen, snack bar, with vinyl floor. Kitchen door to outside 20x24 patio. These areas have exceptional views of the harbor, light house, east bay, and artist point, and daily views of sail, fishing, and orr boats. Three short steps down is a 12x19 living room. Again, the wall pain changes color, another wall of slate, carpet, and exceptional views of the harbor and light house. Off the family room is a short hall with doors to the attached stall and a half garage, 11x11 extra bedroom, main bath with 4x5 tiled shower, 5 foot vanity, and 3 1/2 foot floor to ceiling cabinet, and laundry. And the12x17 master bedroom with 12 feet of closet and walks out to the backyard. A total gut and re-model, everything new, windows, doors, wiring, insolation, trusses, shingles,.... The house sits on 3 2/3 city lots, the 2ed largest private lot on Broadway. There are cherry, apple, cedar, spruce, and lilac trees. Currents, raspberry's, Goya berry's, grape vines, asparagus, chives, flower and vegetable gardens, numerous kinds of trees. Paved parking in front and back. 14x19 detached garage in the paved alley. A large area of the back yard is in-closed by chain link fence. Note: pictures taken before carpet install.

description: For sale: $269,000. Family cabin on Pike lake with super accessible, shared shoreline! The cabin sits very close to the Lake and offers wonderful Lake views. Woodsy interior and veryfunctional floor plan, all on one level. Nice entry way ( mud room ) to take off your snowy or muddy gear, cozy living room with wood burning fireplace and lake view! Kitchen with plenty of shelves and storage, kitchen island and open to the dining area. Master Bedroom is spacious and has access to a deck with views of the lake. The second bedroom will accommodate kids or guests. Laundry room completes the package. The garage has insulated space above, ready for a work shop or art studio. Fire pit on the lake side makes for winter and summer outside gatherings, sipping hot cocoa or roasting marshmallows. Shared septic system and well make for affordable North Woods get-away! There is plenty to do year round, snowmobile and cross country ski trails, snowshoe in the woods, ice fishing! Summer is the prime time with lake living - swimming, fishing, boating, jet skiing or hiking. Superior Hiking trail is right off Pike Lake Road. This is a wonderful cabin and would make a great family retreat or vacation rental.

description: For sale: $329,900. Motivated Seller. This fabulous property has everything you're looking for in a home. description: For sale: $399,000. East of Grand Marais a few minutes flows the Devil Track River. Right where if finds its home in Lake Superior is a home for the ages! Many have appreciated this one of a kind structure on the North Shore. The Stone Home sits right on the river. This is not hyperbole: from the living room window the view is straight down to the river, and itis mesmerizing to watch the river from this vantage. The river bed is wide here, spreading out just as it comes into Superior. In the spring, the volume of water is mindboggling, the raw power invigorating. As the seasons settle so does the water to a more leisurely pace, a thick sheet of calm water cruising over the rocky bed. Keep eyes peeled for the flash and dart of trout. An otter may appear. Then, just to the left see how it enters Superior: sometimes it is over to the west, then to the east. The river and lake shake hands like this, pushing around the beach gravels, shaping their channels. The Stone Home was born as the headquarters of an old time resort, way back in the day. Fisherman and tourists could stop in and get a sandwich or some advice. Today, it is home, a getaway, a place to get back in touch with the rhythms of water, seasons and one's own life. The current owners have carefully and lovingly attended to the home. It is a place of refuge, modern comforts and gathering. It would be an ideal year round home or the cabin. The old hardwood floors are shined up, too bad they can't tell their stories. An updated, class-act kitchen overlooks the river and Big Lake. Beamed ceilings. 3 bedrooms and 3 baths provide plenty of elbow room for the whole gang. The upstairs is private, 2 bedrooms, one with bathroom and large window overlooking the sylvan and aquatic beauty. Family room upstairs, too. Roomy, dry basement for laundry, workshop and storage. A small home owners association is in place: functional and friendly. A couple minutes to Grand Marais. Or even closer, hike the Superior Hiking Tr. Lots to do, or nothing at all. The stones are what make this property: each handpicked and placed with attention to create an exterior siding as impermeable and lasting as the granite from which the rocks derive. A home should be about core values and identity. These stones set the tone: they are out of the core of North America, the deep and stable Canadian Shield underlying all of the North Shore.

description: For sale: $284,900. Don't miss this great cabin located on popular Devil Track Lake! The cabin features wood beams, a main floor open-concept layout, large patio doors that can be opened to create a wonderful indoor/outdoor feel, and large (!) loft space with amazing lake views! Idyllic level yard space - plenty of space for yard games, outdoor dining, and bonfires! Enjoy reading, writing, or playing games in the peaceful screen porch. Walk across the permanent dock to access the lake. The shoreline is wonderfully unique - you'll love this cove of Devil Track and its possibilities for paddle boarding, boating, swimming and more! On the other side of the private road, you'll love the clearing that has already been done - level land at the mouth of privately created trails. Perfect for ATV access, hiking, snowshoeing, and more! Additionally, enjoy the benefits that come with living adjacent to hundred of acres of public land! Close access to the Devil Track Loop... hike and bike until your heart's content! Prefer to snowmobile? Perfect! Pick up the snowmobile trail right across the lake. Winter or summer, enjoy boating to the always-inviting Skyport Lodge, located directly across the lake. Devil Track Lake residents consider themselves lucky to have a great restaurant located right on the lake - there aren't many inland lakefront restaurants in the area! This cabin is located near the west end of the lake and already has a solar power system with back-up generator installed. The refrigerator, stove, oven and on-demand hot water heater all run on propane, along with a space heater; although the wood stove typically generates more than enough heat in the winter. New SSTS installed in 2015. On-demand water heater and water filtration system utilizing lake water installed in lieu of well.

description: For sale: $384,900. Large contemporary home/studio in Grand Marais is ready for your vision. Exterior upkeep has been completed. House was re-stained in 2018 and the roof replaced in 2019. Over 4200 square feet of living space (including studio) on 2 + floors with many large double thermopane (4 plates of glass) windows! There is also a cozy, 1 bedroom apartment on main floor with it's own full size kitchen and fireplace.  This place is SOLIDLY built with full dimension, rough cut lumber, vaulted ceilings, complete with oak beams throughout the interior. The dry basement is useable for extra storage or shop space. Notice the in-floor heat with propane boiler. Gorgeous fireplaces were built by local craftsmen with Pine Mountain stone, complete with oak mantles and circulating heat fans. Includes whole house central vacuum. All kitchen appliances are included as well as washer and dryer. This home has been used commercially as an art studio/gallery with over 900 square feet of space. What is your dream?! The 2nd floor living space has 2 bedrooms, and the first floor has an additional den/guest room. Did I mention the 3rd floor reading/ craft nook with views of the big lake and the ground floor sunroom, laundry and covered deck area? You need to take a look and create your vision for this Grand Marais home within walking distance to hospital, schools, and downtown, yet on the edge of the woods.

description: For sale: $279,000. Gunflint Trail Wilderness Home with views of Gunflint Lake! Newer construction log sided home tucked in to the woods with over 10 acres bordering the Superior National Forest on two sides for plenty of seclusion, hike to your heart's content!  Throw the boat in at the nearby Gunflint Lake landing when you want to hit the water. Newer construction home has Fabulous lake views from the spacious deck, enjoy summer grilling or just relaxing with a book!  And if you don't feel like grilling, walk to dinner at the Gunflint Lodge and Red Paddle Bistro! This home has a fantastic Gunflint Trail location.  Featuring a very functional floor plan, the main level has a fabulous stone fireplace with patio doors on each side and open concept dining and kitchen area. Gourmet kitchen with granite counters, plenty of cabinets and Whirlpool appliances. Lake View Master bedroom with full bathroom and walk in closet is located on the east side of the home for nice sunrises! The west wing includes bunk bedroom with nice Lake views and spacious closet. Another guest bedroom with queen bed, plus walk in closet. Full bathroom in the hallway, completes the guests/kids sleeping area. Plenty of storage throughout the home. A spectacular feature of this home is the screened porch off the lower level of the home, with a hot tub ready for your relaxation after a long day of hiking, or kayaking  and fishing on Gunflint Lake. Looking for a little more rec room space? You will love the potential to finish the lower level! There is a bathroom roughed in already. The high ceilings will make for a comfortable finished space. In place already is a laundry/utility area. Check out the Wildfire Sprinkler protection system, everything you need in your Gunflint Trail Wilderness Getaway!

description: For sale: $449,000. OVER 350 ft of shoreline and a Fabulous home on Pike Lake, located between the Harbor town of Grand Marais and Lutsen! The home features Vaulted Ceilings in the Great room, with stone wood burning fireplace- efficient Opal II insert for heating as well as ambiance as you enjoy BIG views of Pike Lake from the wall of lake facing windows. The dining area opens up to the walk out Deck, a beautiful wrap around allowing you to meander, monitoring the progress of the apple trees and gardens at the entry of the home, as well as the fall leaf colors outlining the ever changing views of Pike Lake.  The kitchen has hickory cabinets, and lots of counter space for preparing family holiday meals! Very functional as is, but at the current price, there's plenty of budget for remodeling!! You'll appreciate the main level bedroom and nice walk through connecting bathroom, but you will LOVE the upper level master bedroom with spectacular loft views of Pike Lake! As if all this wasn't enough, your friends and family will love the lower level walk out to the Lake! Large bedroom, laundry room and bathroom. Awesome Family Rec Room complete with pool table, wood burning stove, and nice Lake views! Let's not forget the Sauna and dressing room, conveniently located near the walk out door to the lake if you want to cool off in the winter months!  The shoreline is prime; rocky along the edges and deep enough to dive off the end of the dock. Grounds are nicely landscaped with camp sites all set for big family gatherings! Asphalt driveway, two and a half car fully insulated and heated garage with attached canning shed, car port and boat mezzanine. All this on nearly 11 acres of Boreal Forest bordering Superior National Forest lands, just 10 minutes to Grand Marais and less than half hour to Lutsen Mountains Ski Resort! Snowmobile and cross country ski from your door, a Must See lake home!

description: For sale: $375,000. Peaceful, tranquil and varied possibilities are thoughts that come to mind as you drive into this spot on the North Shore. Nestled among literally 3500 mature maple trees sits this 2 bedroom, 3 bath home. Birch, maple, white pine, and Western red cedar have been used throughout the home built by local craftsman. The large windows and open floor plan grant a spacious feeling and ability to enjoy the woods from inside. Check out the comfortable kitchen complete with stainless steel appliances, breakfast bar and large pantry for the cook in the family. Spend time on the deck which wraps entirely around the house. On the upper level is the Master bedroom & bath with built-in armoires & stunning views. The lower level is an open slate for you to continue as is or add extra bedrooms. Plumbing is in place for a wet bar too.  In-floor heat on all levels keeps things cozy warm! A 3 stall detached garage provides room for vehicles and toys with space above that could be guest quarters or office.

description: For sale: $850,000. ATTENTION LAKE SUPERIOR BUYERS OR THINKERS ABOUT BEING LAKE SUPERIOR BUYERS!!!  This may well be the most beautiful Lake Superior home available in Cook County right now!!  This is truly a very special home.  Located just east of Grand Marais this custom built half-log sided, half-log paneled home has it all.  Lake Superior views from every room.  The Great Room was made for relaxing or entertaining or both.  The kitchen is to die for and features custom alder cabinets, a climate controlled wine rack, custom slate range top back splash, granite counter tops, top end appliances, Brazilian Chestnut flooring and so much more.  This is not just a kitchen, this is a work of art.  The Great Room also features tile floors and floor to high ceiling windows that afford great views of Lake Superior, the Grand Marais skyline and Artists Point.  The Master Bedroom opens on to the deck and the great expanse of Lake Superior with the same views from the Great Room.  In fact there are Lake Superior views from every room in this spectacular home.    The walk-in closet with custom built in Knotty Alder drawers and the main floor laundry will blow you away.  The home features in-floor heat and air conditioning and has a back up generator wired into the home for emergencies as well as dual fuel in case of a power outage.  I could go on and on; there is nothing this home lacks..  There is very easy access to an easily walkable shoreline; just the thing for evening fires and s'mores.  This magnificent home positively exudes quality and prestige from every corner and is priced dramatically below Cook County estimated market value.  You must see it to appreciate it.

description: Recently sold: $220,000. Seller is open to reasonable offers. Took it off the market for a couple of weeks, to finish the upper Bathroom (all done now, except the trim). Check out the updated photos ? a few other finishing touches were completed! Quality built home set in a lovely Grand Marais neighborhood, on the peaceful east side of town. The large, beautiful wooded double lot provides maximum privacy and country feel, with the convenience of walking distance to schools and downtown. This affordable, energy efficient home is built with Enercept SIPs, high efficiency Uponor/Wirsbo radiant in-floor heating, and large south facing Pella windows providing passive solar gain. The vaulted entry leads to the main level where you?ll find an open plan living room with ample windows to let the outdoors in, large kitchen with beautiful wood cabinets and plenty of room for an island, and dining area with French door access to the backyard. There is also a nice size main level bedroom, a spacious combined 3/4 bathroom, laundry and utility room, lots of storage under the stairs, and a separate mud room with door to the backyard. Total main level living if needed. The upper level has two spacious bedrooms with plenty of closet space, a big full bath, and a huge family room bathed in natural light. The floor plan design allows you to customize, with many possibilities... easily change the large family room into a master suite ( plumbing is really handy to add a Master Bath) , or add 2 more bedrooms, or 1 more bedroom and family room, TV room or office/den. There are interior finishing to be completed, but the hard part is done! Estimates for finishing the interior is approximately $20,000 including labor. This home is a perfect candidate for a renovation loan. Tailor this beautiful home to your family's needs!

description: Recently sold: $267,000. Great Location in Grand Marais! This meticulously maintained home was custom designed with a very appealing floor plan. The design is all about comfort on one level and plenty of space. The guest bedrooms are separated by the Living room in the North wing. The Master Suite is in the South wing with fabulous private ¾ bathroom and hers and his closets.  The open concept kitchen, dining area and living room makes for perfect family and guest gatherings enjoying home-made meals. You'll love the addition done adding a second family room with a cozy fireplace! A great space for everyone to lounge and relax. Custom door leads to the large deck to enjoy the warm summer days. The property consists of 2 lots and a seasonal creek runs off to the East.  Secluded wooded feel so close to town!  There is a 3 car garage with a workshop bench, enough room for vehicles and outdoor toys!  Tons of value in the City, a must see home!

description: Recently sold: $575,000. It is hard to find the words to describe how wonderful and unusual this property is.  It is certainly one of the more unique properties we have offered.  Let's start with the land...three individual lots used as one currently.  The parcels are 4.61, 2.63, and 10.24 acres (please see aerial views) all with views of Lake Superior.  Talk about a recreational paradise.  Don't need that much land?  Sell one or two parcels for significant profit generation.  Now about the views.  Spectacular just does not cover it.  Complete 180 degree views of the Big Lake complete with all the sound and glory that the lake is famous for.  And it is just an easy hop, skip and jump down to the public lake shore.  Now for the home.  The attraction of this home is enhanced by the spacious deck and magnificent landscaping overlooking the lake.  Entertaining? Grilling? Evening beverages or just plain sitting...this space is made for it all.  The kitchen is a gourmet's (or rank amateur's) dream. Granite counter tops, stainless appliances and more.  The great room features a huge floor to ceiling stone fireplace with wood burning stove.  The massive log beams and half log walls truly present that longed for north woods ambiance.  Perhaps the crown jewel is the Master Suite complete with en suite master bath and walk in closet.  You may never want to leave.  Almost the entire home was remodeled after the owners bought it by a highly skilled local craftsman.  But wait; the picture is not yet complete.  Wait until you get a look at the charming timber frame guest cottage featuring panoramic Superior views and it's own deck and deck chairs.  The cabin has a cute living area, full bath, holding tank, loft bedroom and a sliding library ladder to access it.  Your guests will adore this place.  Want more?  How about a free-standing spacious sauna with a window that looks out over Lake Superior.  And last but certainly not least there is a 26 by 24 garage for all the toys.  This property is quite simply amazing and must absolutely be seen to appreciate it.  But plan on spending some time on your private showing...there is a lot to see and marvel at.
Recently sold: $237,500.

description: Recently sold: $360,000. This newer 4-bedroom, 3-bath, 2-story home has a classic northwoods look with wood siding and stone accents. Sitting around the fire pit next to a creek in the wooded backyard will make you feel like you are in the wilderness even though you are only a few blocks from downtown Grand Marais. It is situated in a wonderfully quiet neighborhood on a paved street. Inside is a kitchen and dining area bathed in natural light from ample marvin windows. A large island and stainless steel appliances including a gas range will make this a great place to cook and entertain. Engineered hickory flooring flows from the kitchen through the living room that has a magnificent stone wood-burning fireplace with built-in cabinets on either side. The open staircase leads to two loft bedrooms and a full bath. The basement patio doors lead you from a large family room out to that marvelous backyard. The family room is plumbed to accommodate a wet bar and there is a large walk-in closet. The basement level also has a roomy bedroom and a beautifully tiled 3/4 bath. In the laundry room the front-load washer and dryer are complimented by fresh white custom cabinets and a laundry sink. The 2-stall detached garage is as beautiful as the house. This is a totally move-in-ready masterpiece.

description: For sale: $399,000. East of Grand Marais a few minutes flows the Devil Track River. Right where if finds its home in Lake Superior is a home for the ages! Many have appreciated this one of a kind structure on the North Shore. The Stone Home sits right on the river. This is not hyperbole: from the living room window the view is straight down to the river, and itis mesmerizing to watch the river from this vantage. The river bed is wide here, spreading out just as it comes into Superior. In the spring, the volume of water is mindboggling, the raw power invigorating. As the seasons settle so does the water to a more leisurely pace, a thick sheet of calm water cruising over the rocky bed. Keep eyes peeled for the flash and dart of trout. An otter may appear. Then, just to the left see how it enters Superior: sometimes it is over to the west, then to the east. The river and lake shake hands like this, pushing around the beach gravels, shaping their channels. The Stone Home was born as the headquarters of an old time resort, way back in the day. Fisherman and tourists could stop in and get a sandwich or some advice. Today, it is home, a getaway, a place to get back in touch with the rhythms of water, seasons and one's own life. The current owners have carefully and lovingly attended to the home. It is a place of refuge, modern comforts and gathering. It would be an ideal year round home or the cabin. The old hardwood floors are shined up, too bad they can't tell their stories. An updated, class-act kitchen overlooks the river and Big Lake. Beamed ceilings. 3 bedrooms and 3 baths provide plenty of elbow room for the whole gang. The upstairs is private, 2 bedrooms, one with bathroom and large window overlooking the sylvan and aquatic beauty. Family room upstairs, too. Roomy, dry basement for laundry, workshop and storage. A small home owners association is in place: functional and friendly. A couple minutes to Grand Marais. Or even closer, hike the Superior Hiking Tr. Lots to do, or nothing at all. The stones are what make this property: each handpicked and placed with attention to create an exterior siding as impermeable and lasting as the granite from which the rocks derive. A home should be about core values and identity. These stones set the tone: they are out of the core of North America, the deep and stable Canadian Shield underlying all of the North Shore.
Recently sold: $210,000.

description: Recently sold: $136,000. Cute and comfortable in the heart of Good Harbor Hill.  Nestled below the white pines, this home is just right in its Northwoods setting. Conveniently located on Cty Rd 7, 5 mins to Grand Marais, 5 mins to the Cascade River, heck head up to Pike Lake for a swim or wet a line. Superior Hiking Tr nearby, snowmobile and XC trails close. Hardwood floors warm up the interior, blazing woodstove supplements the heating system. Solid wood siding and mellow wood interior. Lots of natural light. Keep some chickens or turn the coop into a shed or sauna! Wonderful variety of trees. Garden is in and awaiting your vision and seeds.  Ol' timey garage beckons at the road's edge. It's peaceful at a price that is hard to find in Cook County with all the amenities. This is your starter home for the family, or a groovy Grand Marais getaway. Bring home blueberries, jar them here or make a pie. Wintertime, buck and haul wood. Run to town for ice cream or a sixer or both, no problem! Live here, enjoy!

description: Recently sold: $350,000. Imagine enjoying the phenomenal sunsets & totally amazing views Sea Gull Lake from this awesome home! description: Recently sold: $312,500. Here's the cabin of dreams: End of the road, abutting miles of public land, abundant frontage. All of this on big, beautiful, wild Pike Lake. The cabin is laid out for ease and relaxation. Cribbage, woodstove, Sigurd Olson, and good meals are how the days layout inside. Outside, is a gravel shoreline lapped by the crystal clear waters of Pike Lake, an excellent fishery. Swimming here is elemental, takes you back. Still and quiet with nothing for miles to the north and west, except bird call, the wind soughing through the pines, and busy Northwood denizens making their wild living. A sprawling deck oversees it all. Easy distance to Grand Marais when you yearn for the city lights or need a few groceries. But get back soon: head out on the boat, sit on the dock, share a story around the campfire. There's not much else to do: the cabin's in good shape and work is miles away. Unwind, drift a little. Stoke the woodstove. There's plenty of room for family and friends. Take it easy.
